	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. ([- - - -Mete]ll. Denter); Chr. 354 (Tucco et Metello); Fast. Hyd. (Tacio et Dantone); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod. (C. Servilius et L. Caelius); Degrassi 40f., 112, 428f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1042> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1042" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Tucca is restored from the forms in the Chronographers. On Caecilius' name, see also 283, Praetor. On Polyb. 2.19.8, the question of Metellus' death while {Gr}, and the election of M'. Curius to his place, see 283, Praetor; and Degrassi 112." .
